sql:
SELECT iteration_name, status
FROM iterations
ORDER BY iteration_name;

external_knowledge:
- 'chronicles of project milestones' metaphorically refers to the comprehensive details of each iteration; 
- 'birth' and 'duration' refer to the start and end dates of an iteration, respectively; 
- 'model blueprint' is another term for 'model version'; 
- 'completion status' refers to the status of the iteration (e.g., in progress, completed, failed); 
- 'performance overview' refers to the average precision and recall metrics; 
- 'feature complexity' is represented by the number of features used; 
- 'researchers who have delved into them' refers to the number of distinct researchers who accessed each iteration.

sql:
SELECT iteration_name
FROM iterations
ORDER BY iteration_name;

SELECT COUNT(feature_id) AS feature_count
FROM features
WHERE iteration_id = (SELECT iteration_id FROM iterations WHERE iteration_name = 'pos_Overall_Iter#0');

external_knowledge:
- Average accuracy and F-measure are calculated to provide an overall performance score for each iteration; 
- Cumulative true positives and false positives give insight into the researchers' performance over time; 
- Ordering by iteration name and researcher ID is useful for comparing performances across different iterations and researchers.
